---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Values" description="Dangerous Robot's editorial position, plainly stated." layout="reading">
  <article class="reading">
    <h1>Values</h1>

    <p>
      A short manifesto, uncited. Every other page on this site is sourced;
      this page is the editorial position.
    </p>

    <h2>AI safety is unsolved</h2>
    <p>
      Frontier AI is being deployed faster than the field can verify it is
      safe. The plausible failure modes include existential risk. Vendors
      publish responsibility pages, but cannot characterize what their own
      models will do.
    </p>
    <p>
      Dangerous Robot treats every vendor safety claim as a claim, not a fact.
    </p>

    <h2>AI is fueling environmental destruction</h2>
    <p>
      Large AI models burn electricity, water, and embodied carbon at
      industrial scale. Firms are rushing to build fossil fuel-powered data
      centers to win an arms race. The costs are real and worth naming.
    </p>

    <h2>Our contradictions</h2>
    <p>
      Dangerous Robot runs on AI to investigate AI. We critique tools we
      depend on and burn electricity doing it. The contradictions are real,
      and we won't dress them up.
    </p>
    <p>
      We try to be careful: small decisions go to small models, frontier
      models only when the task demands it. Our pipeline runs on Infomaniak,
      a Swiss provider using 100% renewable energy that <a href="https://news.infomaniak.com/en/infomaniak-inaugurates-a-revolutionary-data-center-that-recovers-100-of-its-energy-for-building-heating/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">recovers waste heat
      to warm buildings</a>. It's a small effort, not a solution.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  article h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  article > p:first-of-type {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
</style>
